semiconductor industry：		#Knowledge-intense and captital-intense industry
	design-manufacture-assembly&test
	IDM = design+manufacture+assembly&test
	IPCompany = design(module)
	Fabless = design(assembly|module)
	Foundry = manufacture
	Assembly&TestFoundry = assmebly&test

device-chip-company:
	PC-CPU-Intel/AMD, PC-GPU-Nvidia/AMD, 
	SmartPhone-SOC-Qualcomm/Apple/MediaTek/HiSilicon/SpreadTrum, SmartPhone-CPU(in SOC)-ARM
	PC/SmartPhone-Memory-Toshiba/WesternDigital, PC/SmartPhone-Assembly&Test-ASE, PC/SmartPhone-otherIPChips-manyCompanies
	
Semiconductor Company:
	IDM - integrated device manufactory
		Intel(CPU),Samsung(SOC) | Toshiba,WesternDigital (Memory) | TI[America],ST[EU],infineon[EU],NXP[EU] (OtherIPChips)
		# IDM sometimes provide manufacture service to Fabless company(Samsung - Qualcomm,Apple)
	
	IPCompany
		ARM[EU] | manySmallCompany(OtherIPChips)
		# ARM(RISC) is a CPU architectrue different from the x86(CISC) that Intel and AMD used, mainly used for embedded processor
		
	Fabless/Foundry
		Fabless: Qualcomm,Apple,MediaTek[Taiwan],HiSilicon[Huawei subsidiary],SpreadTrum[shanghai] (SOC) | AMD(CPU,GPU),Nvidia(GPU)
		Foundry: TSMC,UMC[Taiwan],GlobalFoundries[America] {60%,10%,10%}
	
	Assembly&TestFoundry
		Taiwan[ASE],America,MainlandChina {50%,20%,10%}

SOC introduction:
	1) SOC = assamble CPU + OtherIPChips(RAM,GPU,DSP...) into a single chip, mainly used in smartphone
	2) SOC can improve the performance, cost, dissipation, robustness of its IPchips system
	3) notice: SOC do not include all the chips a smart phone need and there are many other chips outside SOC on the motherBoard
	4) Four High-End SOC: Qualcomm-Snapdragon, Apple-Aseries, Samsung-Exynos, Huawei-Kirin 

	
